<span id="freeTextContainer6079971622435354815"> This book started out with so much possibility. A group of old high school friends gathering for a wedding between two of the friends who had found each other again.<br/> It was very interesting to see where each of their lives had taken them. It was interesting to learn of their relationships in high school. There was even a wonderful second story taking place because one of the characters was writing a novel and it was being revealed as she wrote it.<br/> However, the book ended UGLY. It revealed some </span>
  <span id="freeText6079971622435354815" style="display:none"> This book started out with so much possibility. A group of old high school friends gathering for a wedding between two of the friends who had found each other again.<br /> It was very interesting to see where each of their lives had taken them. It was interesting to learn of their relationships in high school. There was even a wonderful second story taking place because one of the characters was writing a novel and it was being revealed as she wrote it.<br /> However, the book ended UGLY. It revealed some really terrible things about most of the people. That in itself would have been okay, but nothing was resolved or no great break throughs were made. In fact several more mistakes were made by the characters that seemed to have no meaning or merit.<br /> Both the real book, and the novel being written just stopped. There was no ending to either. The stories just stopped in really bad situations. Worse yet, I didn't want to know what happen to the characters. I didn't want to know them. I was not endeared to them. <br /></span>
